      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Shortest Words With J — Quick J Plays for Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-07-02">July 2, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The J tile sits in your rack staring at you — 8 points of potential, but hard to deploy on a crowded board. The solution? Short words. Two and three-letter J words let you drop that high-value tile quickly, often on premium squares, without needing a lucky seven-letter rack. Here are all the compact J plays you need to know.</p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points (J tile)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J in the bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">2-letter J word</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">3-letter J words</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Only 2-Letter J Word</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">There's exactly one two-letter word containing J in Scrabble. It's the quickest way to dump your J tile and score reliably.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Essential</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">9 points • 2 letters • SOWPODS + TWL</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A Scottish term of endearment (also spelled "joe"). This is your safety valve — whenever you're stuck with J and the board is tight, JO fits almost anywhere. On a Double Letter Score, the J alone hits 16 points.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Best 3-Letter J Words</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Three-letter J words are your bread and butter. They're short enough to fit on cramped boards but pack serious punch. Here are the top scorers:</p>

