              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Score</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Meaning</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JAW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Part of the mouth; to talk</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JAY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A type of bird</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To ring a bell; a stroke of a bell</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JOY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Great happiness</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JAB</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A quick punch</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JAM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Fruit preserve; to squeeze in</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JOB</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Paid work or task</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JAG</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A sharp projection; a spree</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JIG</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A lively dance</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JOG</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To run slowly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JUG</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A container for liquids</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JET</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A stream of liquid or gas; a plane</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JOT</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To write briefly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">JUT</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To extend outward</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Insight -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Scoring Pattern</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Notice the pattern: J + <span class="text-white font-medium">high-value consonant</span> (W=4, Y=4, B=3, G=2) scores best. JAW/JAY/JOW/JOY all hit 13 because W and Y add 4 points each. Prioritise these when you have the letters.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Strategy</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Short J words shine on premium squares because you're concentrating 8 points into a tiny footprint. Here's how to maximise:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ J on Double Letter</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J becomes 16 points. JO on DLS = 17 total. JAW with J on DLS = 21.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ J on Triple Letter</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J becomes 24 points. JO on TLS = 25 total. Devastating for 2 tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Double Word Score</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JAW on DWS = 26. JOY on DWS = 26. Short words, double everything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Parallel Play</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play JO parallel to an existing word to form 2-3 words simultaneously. J on premium + crossword bonus = huge points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Play Short J Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tight board:</span> When the board is closed and long words don't fit, JO or a 3-letter J word can squeeze into narrow openings for quick points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Late game:</span> With fewer tiles left, short J words prevent getting stuck. Don't hold J hoping for a bingo — dump it efficiently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square access:</span> If you can reach a DLS or TLS with a 2-3 letter word, take it. J on TLS = 24 points from one tile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack balance:</span> J doesn't combine well with other high-value tiles. If your rack has J+Q+Z, get rid of J first with a short play so you can focus on Q/Z placement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Best J Words in Scrabble — full list of high-scoring J plays at every length</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/shortest-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Shortest Words With X — compact high-value X plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/shortest-words-with-z/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
